WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.080
Hi, my name is Mia Cox. I'm a senior at Kipp Sunnyside High School, and I recently found out that I will

00:06.080 --> 00:10.800
be attending Swarthmore College in Pennsylvania, which is my dream college, so I'm very excited.

00:11.600 --> 00:16.560
So I attended the International Space Settlement Design Competition once before 11th grade,

00:16.560 --> 00:21.280
and then I attended the regional competition twice in 9th and 10th grade. And the international

00:21.280 --> 00:27.040
competition is one of my greatest high school memories, experiences. Going into it I was very

00:27.040 --> 00:33.280
intimidated, very nervous because I felt so unprepared when I was in the regional competition,

00:33.280 --> 00:38.880
but going to internationals makes it all worth it because there's a greater emphasis on teamwork

00:38.880 --> 00:44.160
and building friendships. There's so many people from all over the world, and we have to learn

00:44.160 --> 00:51.360
from each other despite any language barriers or cultural barriers or barriers of understanding.

00:51.360 --> 00:57.600
And it was very fun, and I made so many friends, and so I 100% recommended. And then initially,

00:57.600 --> 01:02.480
I didn't really know how to answer this question because I'm going to major in psychology or

01:02.480 --> 01:08.640
sociology and then go down a criminology path. And I was like, how did the competition really

01:08.640 --> 01:14.160
impact that? Then I remembered every year I participated in the humanities group, and if

01:14.160 --> 01:20.400
not for COVID, I would have been able to run as a director for humanities. And I realized that

01:20.400 --> 01:26.160
putting myself in that group, there's so many books from the library I had to read. So researching

01:26.160 --> 01:31.840
more about humans and what we would need to survive and really taking that into account,

01:31.840 --> 01:36.720
something that we just do day by day and not realize, plus the aspect of, in the international

01:36.720 --> 01:42.560
competition, learning so much from so many different people made me love humanities so much more. And

01:42.560 --> 01:48.560
so I'm really appreciative of the competition. I made so many friends. I've met so many interesting

01:48.560 --> 01:53.920
people, and now I'm to attend my dream college and study something I'm very passionate about.

01:54.480 --> 01:58.800
So thank you for listening, and thank you for the great experiences I was able to have

01:58.800 --> 01:59.840
through the competition.

